    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans heavily on high-ceiling matchups against pitchers with elevated expected ERAs. **James Wood** (75.94) stands out as our top play, capitalizing on a prime leadoff spot and a favorable matchup against a vulnerable arm; he is the clear centerpiece of our offensive strategy. Close behind him, **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (75.73) provide elite efficiency scores driven by aggressive park factors and favorable platoon splits. **Mickey Moniak** specifically benefits from an impressive 14% boost due to dynamic platoon advantages, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** continues to be a focal point for his rare speed-power combination, even with a minor efficiency dip caused by the opponent's catcher framing.\n\nWe are hunting stolen bases today, which makes the benching of **Austin Riley** (44.64) a strategic necessity rather than a reflection of his talent. While **Austin Riley** remains a powerhouse, his projected efficiency fell just short of our threshold today due to a clash with a formidable left-handed arm, which suppressed his raw numbers. Elsewhere, **Trevor Story** (67.62) provides significant upside against the exploitable Drohan, despite a 5% penalty from wind conditions. We are monitoring **Corbin Carroll** closely; his 64.19 score remains respectable, but he is fighting uphill against a difficult Peterson, D and a slight negative park factor. As always, keep an eye on our reserves like **Seiya Suzuki**, **Brice Turang**, **Dalton Rushing**, **Carson Williams**, **Gabriel Arias**, and **Travis Bazzana** for potential pinch-hit opportunities if any of our starters are pulled late due to blowout scenarios or unfavorable late-inning defensive switches.",
